{"title_page": "Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games", "text_new": "{{short description|The Karate competitions at the 2019 Pan American Games}}\n{{Infobox Pan American Games event\n|event = Karate\n|games = 2019\n|image = Karate 2019 Pan American Games.png\n|image_size = 100\n|caption = Karate pictogram\n|venue = [[Polideportivo Villa El Salvador]]\n|dates = August 9\u201311, 2019\n|competitors = 132\n|nations = \n|prev = [[Karate at the 2015 Pan American Games|2015]]\n|next = [[Karate at the 2023 Pan American Games|2023]]\n}}\n{{Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games}}\n'''[[Karate]]''' competitions at the '''[[2019 Pan American Games]]''' in [[Lima]], Peru are scheduled to be held between August 9th and 11th, 2019 at the Polideportivo Villa El Salvador, which will also host the [[Gymnastics at the 2019 Pan American Games|gymnastics]] competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lima2019.s3.amazonaws.com/images/panamericanos-en-13-06-19.pdf|title=Pan American Schedule|date=13 June 2019|website=www.lima2019.pe|publisher=Lima Organizing Committee for the 2019 Pan and Parapan American Games (COPAL)|access-date=16 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n14 medal events are scheduled to be contested. Ten of these events are in [[kumite]] (five per gender). A further four events (two per gender) in [[kata]] will be contested, after the [[Pan American Sports Organization|Panamsports]] added them to the sports program in March 2017. This will mark the first time kata events are held at the [[Pan American Games]] since [[2003 Pan American Games|2003]] in [[Santo Domingo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pkfkarate.com/news/notice-to-visitors-pan-american-games-lima-2019/|title=Notice to visitors :Pan American Games Lima 2019|date=4 March 2017|website=www.pkfkarate.com/|publisher=[[Panamerican Karate Federation]]|access-date=29 May 2018}}</ref> A total of 132 athletes will qualify to compete at the games.<ref name=manual/>\n\nThe top three medallists (in order of gold, silver then bronze) not already qualified for the [[2020 Summer Olympics]] according to the Olympic Standings as of April 6, 2020, will qualify for the said games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wkf.net/pdf/olympic/Tokyo2020-QualificationSystem.pdf|title=World Karate Federation (WKF) Qualification System \u2013 Games of the XXXII Olympiad \u2013 Tokyo 2020|date=9 May 2018|website=www.wkf.net/|publisher=[[World Karate Federation]] (WKF)|access-date=28 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630155533/https://wkf.net/pdf/olympic/Tokyo2020-QualificationSystem.pdf|archive-date=30 June 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<!--==Competition schedule==\n[[File:RoyalCanadianYacht.jpg|thumb|right|The [[Royal Canadian Yacht Club]] was the venue for the Karate competitions.]]\nThe following is the competition schedule for the Karate competitions:\n\n{{2019 Pan American Games Karate Schedule}}-->\n\n==Medal table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = PER\n | flag_template  = flagPASO\n | event          = 2019\n | team  \n | gold_USA = 5 | silver_USA = 1 | bronze_USA = 1\n | gold_DOM = 3 | silver_DOM = 1 | bronze_DOM = 3\n | gold_VEN = 2 | silver_VEN = 2 | bronze_VEN = 4\n | gold_PER = 2 | silver_PER = 0 | bronze_PER = 4 | host_PER = yes\n | gold_BRA = 1 | silver_BRA = 2 | bronze_BRA = 4\n | gold_CHI = 1 | silver_CHI = 2 | bronze_CHI = 1\n | gold_MEX = 0 | silver_MEX = 4 | bronze_MEX = 2\n | gold_CAN = 0 | silver_CAN = 2 | bronze_CAN = 0\n | gold_COL = 0 | silver_COL = 0 | bronze_COL = 2\n | gold_GUA = 0 | silver_GUA = 0 | bronze_GUA = 2\n | gold_ARG = 0 | silver_ARG = 0 | bronze_ARG = 1\n | gold_CUB = 0 | silver_CUB = 0 | bronze_CUB = 1\n | gold_PAN = 0 | silver_PAN = 0 | bronze_PAN = 1\n | gold_URU = 0 | silver_URU = 0 | bronze_URU = 1\n}}\n\n==Medallists==\n===Men's events===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2| Individual kata<br/>{{DetailsLink|Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's individual kata}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Antonio D\u00