ez]]|MEX|2019}}\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Cheili Gonz\u00e1lez]]|GUA|2019}}\n|-\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[J\u00e9ssica de Paula]]|BRA|2019}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 55&nbsp;kg<br/>{{DetailsLink|Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's 55 kg}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Val\u00e9ria Kumizaki]]|BRA|2019}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Kathryn Campbell (karateka)|Kathryn Campbell]]|CAN|2019}}\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Baurelys Torres]]|CUB|2019}}\n|-\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Paula Flores]]|MEX|2019}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 61&nbsp;kg<br/>{{DetailsLink|Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's 61 kg}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Alexandra Grande]]|PER|2019}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Claudymar Garc\u00e9s]]|VEN|2019}}\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Karina D\u00edaz]]|DOM|2019}}\n|-\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Xhunashi Caballero]]|MEX|2019}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 68&nbsp;kg<br/>{{DetailsLink|Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's 68 kg}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Tanya Rodr\u00edguez]]|DOM|2019}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Susana Li]]|CHI|2019}}\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Wendy Mosquera]]|COL|2019}}\n|-\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Marianth Cuervo]]|VEN|2019}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2| +68&nbsp;kg<br/>{{DetailsLink|Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's +68 kg}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Pamela Rodr\u00edguez (karateka)|Pamela Rodr\u00edguez]]|DOM|2019}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Omaira Molina]]|VEN|2019}}\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Cirrus Lingl]]|USA|2019}}\n|-\n|{{flagPASOmedalist|[[Isabel Aco]]|PER|2019}}\n|}\n\n==Qualification==\n{{Main|Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games \u2013 Qualification}}\nA total of 132 karatekas will qualify to compete. Each nation may enter a maximum of 18 athletes (nine per gender). There will be eight athletes qualified in each individual event, along with six teams in the kata team events. This consists of a maximum of one athlete in the individual events (12), and one group of three in each kata team event (six). The host nation, Peru, automatically qualifies the maximum number of athletes (18). The rest of the spots will be awarded across four qualification tournaments.<ref name=manual>{{cite web|url=http://www.panamsports.org/downloads/pdf/qualification-system-manual-lima-2019.pdf|title=Qualification System manual|date=25 April 2018|website=www.panamsports.org/|publisher=[[Pan American Sports Organization]]|access-date=29 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Karate at the 2020 Summer Olympics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.panamsports.org/downloads/pdf/lima-2019/KT_Results_Book_1.0.pdf Results book]\n\n{{Pan American Games Karate}}\n{{Events at the 2019 Pan American Games}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karate At The 2019 Pan American Games}}\n[[Category:Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games|Karate at the 2019]]\n[[Category:Events at the 2019 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:2019 in karate|Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:Karate at the Pan American Games|2019]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|The Karate competitions at the 2019 Pan American Games}}\n{{Infobox Pan American Games event\n|event = Karate\n|games = 2019\n|image = Karate 2019 Pan American Games.png\n|image_size = 100\n|caption = Karate pictogram\n|venue = [[Polideportivo Villa El Salvador]]\n|dates = August 9\u201311, 2019\n|competitors = 132\n|nations = \n|prev = [[Karate at the 2015 Pan American Games|2015]]\n|next = [[Karate at the 2023 Pan American Games|2023]]\n}}\n{{Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games}}\n'''[[Karate]]''' competitions at the '''[[2019 Pan American Games]]''' in [[Lima]], Peru are scheduled to be held between August 9th and 11th, 2019 at the Polideportivo Villa El Salvador, which will also host the [[Gymnastics at the 2019 Pan American Games|gymnastics]] competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lima2019.s3.amazonaws.com/images/panamericanos-en-13-06-19.pdf|title=Pan American Schedule|date=13 June 2019|website=www.lima2019.pe|publisher=Lima Organizing Committee for the 2019 Pan and Parapan American Games (COPAL)|access-date=16 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n14 medal events are scheduled to be contested. Ten of these events are in [[kumite]] (five per gender). A further four events (two per gender) in [[kata]] will be contested, after the [[Pan American Sports Organization|Panamsports]] added them to the sports program in March 2017. This will mark the first time kata events are held at the [[Pan American Games]] since [[2003 Pan American Games|2003]] in [[Santo Domingo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pkfkarate.com/news/notice-to-visitors-pan-american-games-lima-2019/|title=Notice to visitors :Pan American Games Lima 2019|date=4 March 2017|website=www.pkfkarate.com/|publisher=[[Panamerican Karate Federation]]|access-date=29 May 2018}}</ref> A total of 132 athletes will qualify to compete at the games.<ref name=manual/>\n\nThe top three medallists (in order of gold, silver than bronze) not already qualified for the [[2020 Summer Olympics]] according to the Olympic Standings as of April 6, 2020, will qualify for the said games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wkf.net/pdf/olympic/Tokyo2020-QualificationSystem.pdf|title=World Karate Federation (WKF) Qualification System \u2013 Games of the XXXII Olympiad \u2013 Tokyo 2020|date=9 May 2018|website=www.wkf.net/|publisher=[[World Karate Federation]] (WKF)|access-date=28 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630155533/https://wkf.net/pdf/olympic/Tokyo2020-QualificationSystem.pdf|archive-date=30 June 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<!--==Competition schedule==\n[[File:RoyalCanadianYacht.jpg|thumb|right|The [[Royal Canadian Yacht Club]] was the venue for the Karate competitions.]]\nThe following is the competition schedule for the Karate competitions:\n\n{{2019 Pan American Games Karate Schedule}}-->\n\n==Medal table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = PER\n | flag_template  = flagPASO\n | event          = 2019\n | team  \n | gold_USA = 5 