le Ratings: 'American Horror Story' Wins Night + 'The Game', 'Duck Dynasty', 'Workaholics' & More|work=TV by the Numbers|date=January 16, 2015|accessdate=January 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Victoria's father Alex ([[Stacy Keach]]), also an actor, comes to town with news that he has three months to live. He tells his daughter that his dying wish is to play one more role on the screen, so Victoria manages to get him a part on her HBO series. Joy then overhears a phone conversation and finds out that Victoria's dad is clearly NOT dying, and he just lied to get work. Meanwhile, Melanie decides that Jack is far too clingy and wants to break up. She gets some advice from her co-worker Franky on how to handle the breakup, but it backfires.\n| LineColor       = B10C28\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Hot in Cleveland (season 6)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 114\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = We Could Be Royals\n| DirectedBy      = Andy Cadiff\n| WrittenBy       = [[Sam Johnson and Chris Marcil|Sam Johnson & Chris Marcil]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|1|21}}\n| ProdCode        = 610\n| Viewers         = 0.95<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-25-wednesday-cable-originals-1-21-2015.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 25 Wednesday Cable Originals (& Network Update): 1.21.2015|publisher=ShowBuzzDaily|date=January 22, 2015|accessdate=January 24, 2015}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Elka and Mamie Sue prepare for the arrival of the British Earl of Cleveland, who is coming to town. Joy's younger sister Jill ([[Sophie Winkleman]]), who recently left a convent, also arrives for a visit. The two vie for the attention of the Earl, but a series of accidents puts Joy at a disadvantage. Meanwhile, Victoria asks Melanie to help her meet a deadline on a children's book, not telling her that she received an advance on the book two years ago. Stumped for ideas, the two base the story on the competition between Joy and Jill.\n| LineCol