, so Joy does all she can to stop Bob from marrying Canadian Joy. Elka has one final sexual fling with the mayor before breaking up with him, only to have the mayor die in bed with her. As the sitting City Council President, Elka becomes mayor. Elsewhere, Victoria is convinced a paparazzi drone is following her, so she hires Bob's brother Claude ([[Brian Baumgartner]]) as her bodyguard to give the impression of not wanting the attention.\n| LineColor       = B10C28\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Hot in Cleveland (season 6)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 117\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n| Title           = Scandalous\n| DirectedBy      = [[Phill Lewis]]\n| WrittenBy       = Lisa Slopey\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|3|18}}\n| ProdCode        = 613\n| Viewers         = 0.86<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/03/19/wednesday-cable-ratings-catfish-wins-night-nba-basketball-dual-survivor-little-women-lamob-wives-the-americans-more/376979/|title=Wednesday Cable Ratings: 'Catfish' Wins Night, NBA Basketball, 'Dual Survivor', 'Little Women LA','Mob Wives', 'Broad City' & More|work=TV by the Numbers|date=March 19, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = When a police detective is assigned to clear up some of the questions surrounding the former mayor's death, new mayor Elka hires her own detectives (Bob and Joy) to act as \"cleaners\" and help her avoid a scandal. But there's one other loose end: a nosy reporter named Dane ([[William Baldwin|Billy Baldwin]]) whom Melanie is assigned to distract. Meanwhile, Victoria sweats over a focus group broadcast in Cleveland for her new HBO series, which will determine if the series airs or not - and the woman badmouthing her is one of the mayor's mistresses. Newly-dating couple Joy and Bob can't seem to find the right moment for their first kiss.\n| LineColor       = B10C28\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Hot in Cleveland (season 6)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 118\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n| Title           = Family Affair\n| DirectedBy      = Dennis Capps\n| WrittenBy       = [[Alex Herschlag]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|3|25}}\n| ProdCode        = 614\n| Viewers         = 0.74<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-25-wednesday-cable-originals-3-25-2015.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 25 Wednesday Cable Originals (& Network Update): 3.25.2015|publisher=ShowBuzzDaily|date=March 26, 2015|accessdate=March 30, 2015}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Melanie gets DNA from the girls' toothbrushes to surprise them with their genealogies and family histories. The results show that: Joy and Elka have a common ancestor from Poland as well as a distant relative who is a waitress in the area, Victoria is 1/32nd Native American, and Melanie has a distant cousin working as a therapist in Cleveland. Victoria tries to gain publicity by joining an Ohio Native American group, only to find that they want to use her to protest [[Chief Wahoo]], the [[Cleveland Indians]] mascot. Melanie makes an appointment with her therapist cousin ([[Timothy Omundson]]) and finds that he is adorable, making her want to find out just how close of a cousin he is.\n| LineColor       = B10C28\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Hot in Cleveland (season 6)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 119\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n| Title           = All Dolled Up\n| DirectedBy      = Andy Cadiff\n| WrittenBy       = Jessica Wood\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|4|1}}\n| ProdCode        = 615\n| Viewers         = 0.82<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-25-wednesday-cable-originals-4-1-2015.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 25 Wednesday Cable Originals (& Network Update): 4.1.2015|publisher=ShowBuzzDaily|date=April 2, 2015|accessdate=April 6, 2015}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = While Bob is away in Canada, he sends Joy a creepy doll that looks like him to keep her company. The girls then think the doll has voodoo powers when strange things start happening t