f the questions surrounding the former mayor's death, new mayor Elka hires her own detectives (Bob and Joy) to act as \"cleaners\" and help her avoid a scandal. But there's one other loose end: a nosy reporter named Dane ([[William Baldwin|Billy Baldwin]]) whom Melanie is assigned to distract. Meanwhile, Victoria sweats over a focus group broadcast in Cleveland for her new HBO series, which will determine if the series airs or not - and the woman badmouthing her is one of the mayor's mistresses. Newly-dating couple Joy and Bob can't seem to find the right moment for their first kiss.\n| LineColor       = B10C28\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Hot in Cleveland (season 6)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 118\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n| Title           = Family Affair\n| DirectedBy      = Dennis Capps\n| WrittenBy       = [[Alex Herschlag]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|3|25}}\n| ProdCode        = 614\n| Viewers         = 0.74<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-25-wednesday-cable-originals-3-25-2015.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 25 Wednesday Cable Originals (& Network Update): 3.25.2015|publisher=ShowBuzzDaily|date=March 26, 2015|accessdate=March 30, 2015}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Melanie gets DNA from the girls' toothbrushes to surprise them with their genealogies and family histories. The results show that: Joy and Elka have a common ancestor from Poland as well as a distant relative who is a waitress in the area, Victoria is 1/32nd Native American, and Melanie has a distant cousin working as a therapist in Cleveland. Victoria tries to gain publicity by joining an Ohio Native American group, only to find that they want to use her to protest [[Chief Wahoo]], the [[Cleveland Indians]] mascot. Melanie makes an appointment with her therapist cousin ([[Timothy Omundson]]) and finds that he is adorable, making her want to find out just how close of a cousin he is.\n| LineColor       = B10C28\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Hot in Cleve